This paper is about a new algorithmic framework for multi-agent reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the competitive pressures arising from growing and shrinking population size, which is related to game theory (cs.GT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the paper mentions potential gains from specialization and division of labor, which is related to systems and control (cs.SY).
